 eventsArcheryAthleticsBoxingFencingJudoSwimmingWeightliftingWrestlingTeam GamesBadmintonBasketballFootballHockeyTable TennisTennisVolleyballRugbyKabaddiVarious top athletes from various universities will participate in KIUG 2020 Games to be held in KIIT University, Bhubaneshwar, Odisha.Participating Athletes List (University Wise) in Khelo India University Games 2020The 1st Khelo India University Games (KIUG-2020 Odisha) will comprise of 4,000 athletes from around 80-100 universities apart from technical and supporting staff. The complete list of participating athletes (university wise) for Khelo India University Games 2020 can be checked using the link:- https://universitygames.kheloindia.gov.in/static-assets/pdfs/Athletes%20data%20university%20wise.pdfKIUG 2020 Odisha Venue DetailsKIIT has already developed a sports environment which is comparable to international standards and gives a truly global experience to athletes at campus. Sports activity in KIIT is facilitated by KIIT Stadium, 12 sports complexes with state-of-the-art swimming pools, outdoor courts, multi-purpose halls, and indoor stadiums distributed in different campuses. The venue for Khelo India University Games 2020 is spread over an area of 29 acre.KIIT Stadium has the capacity to hold day and night matches and is a regular venue for Ranji Trophy matches. Athletes will have access to all ultra-modern sports facilities and training equivalent to any national level sports hostel or sports training centre at the deemed university. Moreover, athletes will also have access to hostel, transport and medical facilities alongwith campus security and gymnasium. Athletes can even explore the cultural heritage of Odisha and visit tourist destination after their games. The central govt. is going to make arrangements for sightseeing.Khelo India University Games (KIUG) 2020 Live TelecastTo make this KIUG 2020 games a success, govt. will take event to people via television, digital streaming and other mediums. Doordarshan is the official broadcaster of first Khelo India University Games (KIUG) 2020. The govt. wants to reach a large number of audience across the nation through live telecast of the games. The govt. even plans to live telecast KIUG 2020 through social platforms and YouTube channels.Our Sports Odisha social handler collectively has subscribers base of around 6 lakh people. In addition to this, social campaigns of KIIT, SAI, and participating universities will significantly add traction for KIUG Odisha 2020. Furthermore, there would be a dedicated event page set up prior to the commencement of the games. It will provide schedules, event updates, photos and highlights of the games.Benefits of Khelo India University Games Odisha 2020The sports events and tournaments are for absolute fun with opportunities to develop sporting skills and relationships with others. The 1st Khelo India University Games Odisha 2020 will see a massive scale involvement of youth. The participants will demonstrate highest level of sportsmanship and return to their states as ambassadors for KIUG and Odisha. All the athletes who shines in these events will get a chance to raise their careers to next level by recognition and better access to guidance and training.Why Odisha is Hosting Khelo India Youth Games?Odisha is already hosting various elite sports events for the last few years. These includes Asian Athletics Championships, Men\u2019s Hockey World Cup, Commonwealth Table Tennis Championships, FIH Series Finals and Hockey Olympic Qualifiers. Khelo India University Games (KIUG) 2020 will create multi-sport opportunity for participation of university athletes. Moreover, the candidates can test and compare their sporting talent level against the various competitors across India. The main objective is to create culture of sports in community, build the value of sports in the higher education sector and contribute to a healthy and FIT society.The 1st Khelo India University Games (KIUG) is organized by the Odisha govt. in association with the Sports Authority of India (SAI), Association of Indian Universities, National Sports Federation and Indian Olympic Association (IOA) and other participating universities. KIUG first edition is focused on identification of talented athletes and nurture talent through guidance and developed infrastructure.Over the past few years, #Bhubaneswar has emerged as the sports capital of India hosting some big sporting events. The city is ready for another marquee sports event. The first edition of the Khelo India University Games will be held in the city next month. #OdishaForSports pic.twitter.com/rB3xpH6MXN\u2014 Odisha Sports (@sports_odisha) January 6, 2020 Odisha Hero Gold Cup 4-Nation Women\u2019s Football TournamentOdisha has received a provisional clearance to host FIFA U17 Women\u2019s World Cup 2020. Now the young girls of India can take the sport of football with more zest and produce international women footballers. Before World Cup, Odisha govt. will start Women\u2019s Football League with the format potentially expanding over the next 5 years to cover all youth football age categories. The Odisha govt. also plans to undertake other steps at the community level to encourage young girls to take up the sport.  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now Source / Reference Link: https://sportstar.thehindu.com/other-sports/khelo-india-university-games-2020-odisha-bhubaneswar-sports-minister-tusharkanti-behera/article30485367.ece  at  "}